---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Egypt Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/egypt/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Morocco for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/morocco' },
  { title: 'Turkey for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/turkey' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'egyptFit', header: 'Egypt Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'EGP$15,000-21,400/mo', egyptFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'EGP$17,550-25,070/mo', egyptFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'EGP$13,500-19,280/mo', egyptFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'EGP$12,550-17,930/mo', egyptFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Allianz Egypt, AXA)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'EGP$2,000-6,000/mo', egyptFit: 'Regional' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'EGP$13,500-21,400', annual: 'EGP$162K-256.8K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'EGP$18,520-28,550', annual: 'EGP$222.2K-342.6K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'EGP$24,900-38,350', annual: 'EGP$298.8K-460.2K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'EGP$500-1,500/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'EGP$3,000-8,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Egypt 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Egypt. Pyramids, Nile cruises, affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Egypt"
  subheadline="Egypt offers ancient wonders, Nile River beauty, extremely affordable living, Red Sea beaches, and warm hospitality—timeless destination for history lovers and sun seekers."
  heroImage="/images/countries/egypt-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Egypt</h2>
  <p>
    Egypt offers Pyramids, pharaonic history, Nile cruises, Red Sea diving, and extremely affordable living. For history-loving retirees seeking ancient wonders with low costs and warm climate, Egypt provides unmatched cultural wealth at remarkable value.
  </p>

  <p>
    Cairo is the capital with best healthcare but intense. Alexandria offers Mediterranean lifestyle. Luxor provides pharaonic immersion. Hurghada and Sharm el-Sheikh have Red Sea resort communities. Many expats choose coastal towns for quieter lifestyle with Cairo healthcare accessible.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Private good; affordable; improving</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; English in tourism/business</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> EGP$25,000-50,000/month (~$500-1,000 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Hot dry; Mediterranean north; desert south</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Ancient history; hospitality; bustling</li>
      <li><strong>Value:</strong> Extraordinary purchasing power</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Egypt Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Egypt has good private healthcare—As-Salam International Hospital and Cairo private hospitals provide modern care at affordable prices. Many doctors trained internationally. Public system basic. Most conditions treatable locally; complex cases may go to Dubai or Europe.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare very affordable by Western standards. Quality improving rapidly. International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage and regional access. Good value proposition for healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Affordable Quality Healthcare</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Egypt offers good private healthcare at low cost. Cairo has excellent hospitals. Most conditions treatable locally. Dubai provides backup for complex cases. International insurance provides comprehensive coverage and peace of mind.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Egypt has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30 days visa on arrival or e-visa. Simple process. Extensions available.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Up to 3-6 months with extensions. Many use repeated tourist visas.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For longer stays. Various categories. Property ownership helps. Apply through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Retirement Residence</h3>
  <p>
    With proof of income/pension. Relatively straightforward process.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Egypt:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> Dubai/Europe coverage for complex cases</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Egypt</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage. Local private care is good and affordable. Dubai provides excellent backup for complex cases. Good combination of local accessibility and international security.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Egypt, regional coverage with international backup:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Egypt</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Middle East network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Dubai access:</strong> Regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>Local value:</strong> Affordable quality care available</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Egypt retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Egypt (EGP ~50 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Local private:</strong> Excellent value healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Middle East focused</li>
    <li><strong>Cairo network:</strong> Use designated hospitals</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: History Enthusiast, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month pension. Residence permit. Luxor.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Cairo/Dubai backup.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~EGP$16,000/month (~$320). Pharaonic immersion; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Red Sea Diver, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,200/month pension. Tourist rotation. Hurghada.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Europe coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~EGP$20,000/month (~$400). Resort lifestyle; global backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Mediterranean Retiree, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,500/month Social Security. Residence permit. Alexandria.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with regional coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~EGP$14,000/month (~$280). Coastal living; affordable coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Egypt safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—tourist areas well-protected. Red Sea resorts very secure. Cairo can be intense but not dangerous. Avoid Sinai desert borders. Political situation stable currently. Tourism is national priority. Normal precautions apply.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Arabic?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful but not essential—English widely spoken in tourism, business, healthcare. Arabic learning opens more experiences. Tourist areas fully accessible in English. Daily life easier with some Arabic phrases.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Egypt really that affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—currency devaluation made Egypt extremely affordable. $500-1,000/month covers comfortable life. Healthcare very cheap. Restaurants, services, housing all affordable. One of world's best value destinations currently.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the climate like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Hot and dry—summer (Jun-Aug) very hot (40°C+). Winter (Nov-Feb) pleasant. Alexandria cooler Mediterranean. Red Sea warm year-round. Low humidity makes heat bearable. AC essential summer months.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Egypt coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Egypt authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
